annotation.TEXT: Being shrunk is going to make getting coins in the sky bonus area tougher...
Nuts. I wanted to clobber Lakitu with a brick directly. Oh, well. I'll have some more chances to do so later in this level.

Okay, so I'm glad to have a character that can move quickly for this level, because there are four bonus areas here that I'm gonna want to check out, and I was concerned that a slower character might have time limit issues with doing this.
Demo count: 5
Yeah, you couldn't jump away from a wall with that much force in the original Blaster Master. But, maybe one or more of the sequels added that function. I don't know.
If the "kick the shell on the stairs for 1-ups" trick worked in SMB Crossover, I might've tried it there.

A trash can? Aw, it replaced my wheel! Well, maybe it's not all bad, since it functions like the axe, and that's not a bad subweapon (I prefer the axe over the boomerang in certain situations in the Castlevania games).
Lakitu sure can take a lot of punishment before going down, and he respawns so quickly afterwards.
Whoops, that's not the Super Arm... Okay, here we go.
D'oh! I got unlucky with that flame there. And with that hit, my chain whip powered down to just a stick. However, at least I still have my trash can!
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Now, I'm going to use some of the above voted-for characters to play through world 6 here, but which ones?
Hmm... Well, maybe I can still get all of the coins...

Square fireworks FTW!
BARF!
Sweet, I got my first (and last) sky bonus perfect of this playthrough!
D'oh, I overshot, and d'oh, I didn't want to fall there... Argh!
Alright, now it's time for me to go with Simon for 6-4. Now, there were alt. skin votes for Richter and Alex. I think I'll go with Alex to be radically different.
Alright, now let's see if I can do better in the sky bonus area this time...
There's no gameplay differences between him and Simon, but his weapons look different. It looks like I'm throwing a wheel for the boomerang.
Oh, come on! That hit me?! Argh, the piranha plant hitboxes were so much more generous in the original SMB (but, to be fair, they weren't so generous in the All-Stars version).
MOON!!! ...Actually, that's just a regular "fire flower" power up, not something that gives me a 3-up. But still, MOON!!!
I did get 13 coins from that block though, which isn't terrible.
Alright, it's boss time, against the NES SMB1 Bowser, who's started tossing hammers now that I'm in world 6! Well, I have my own attack that travels in an arc!
Sweet! For the third time today, I've gotten the 5000 and the 6 fireworks!
Also, it costs less to use here. In SMB Crossover, the boomerang costs 2 hearts to use, but the axe only costs 1.
Interesting... And the fragments hit the multi-coin block below me a couple times. I'm... probably not gonna get 15 coins from that block.
Also, why are those three stone blocks there under the exit pipe? They don't affect gameplay at all, but I'm still wondering why they're there.
Oh! I can't defeat the Bullet Beezos with my regular shot, but the 3-way missiles work! What about the homing missiles?
Alright, let's try this again, but with the Super Demon Returns version of the Demon Prince this time.
Nice, got the 5000 and the 6 fireworks.
Sky bonus perfect count: 1
At least Protoman can still charge his buster without a mushroom. I just can't fire more than 2 shots at the same time right now.

Well, I'm probably not gonna Wall Climb all that much, especially since Hover ability is probably way better most of the time in this SMB environment. Also, I'm not gonna risk breaking any balance lifts now, even if I could Hover out of danger.
I wonder if Thunder Break would work, but I haven't seen any Thunder Break pickups yet. Are there Thunder Break pickups for Sophia III in SMB Crossover?
Alright, it's nice to know that these hidden blocks are in the right spots.
Whew, got him! I was worried that I'd run out of time or weapon energy here.
Now, since I'm using a character that can swim, this area shouldn't be too big of a problem, especially since I can "blow away" the sea life!
(I would kind of like to try some of the other differently-functioning Mega Man and Bass skins that I haven't tried yet.)
Oh, we've got something new here. It appears to be the "Wall 1" ability, but with additional functionality that wasn't in the original NES Blaster Master.
Man, the timing is really tricky here.

So, we're gonna be a different kind of blocky tank!

Ack! Once again I fell through the hole while trying to run across it! It's not a problem with me not holding X to run, because the X key has been working perfectly for me so far. I think it's due to the fact that Mario's movement physics aren't quite right in SMB Crossover.
To be continued...
Oh, neat. It sounds like the music out here continued right from where it left off.

Oh, and the alt. skin votes include: Cut Man/Ice Man/Rokko Chan (Mega Man), Quick Man (Bass), Demon Prince (Mario), Alex (Simon), and Richter (Simon). I'm gonna start with Random here...
